This paper deals with video-based face recognition, which is a computer vision problem, hence it is likely to belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) category. The paper proposes a graphical model for identity propagation between tracklets, which involves uncertainty modeling, indicating that it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category. The paper also mentions the use of state-of-the-art results, which suggests that it could belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) category. The paper involves the use of contextual connections and uncertainty modeling, which are common themes in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) research. Finally, the paper deals with the problem of erroneous information propagation, which is a security concern, indicating that it could also belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) category.
